   Mrs. Papandreou, who heads Greece's largest feminist
organization, is expected to make a brief stopover today in Milan,
Italy, to attend a conference of the European Socialist and Leftist
Women.
   Papandreou who will celebrate his 70th birthday on Sunday, has
been living with his 34-year-old girlfriend, former airline
stewardess Dimitra Liani.
   He is expected to marry Ms. Liani, herself twice divorced, when
his marriage is officially dissolved. It would be Papandreou's third
marriage.
   Mrs. Papandreou responded by accusing the premier of distorting
the truth and said that ``the premier and I decided to meet after my
return from the United States.''
