<FIRST>r i PM-Vietnam-Missing     02-04 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Vietnam-Missing,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Vietnam Sets Up Office To Search For Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vietnam has set up a service to search
for missing relatives and families apart from its ongoing effort to
locate Americans missing in action from the Indochina war, the
Vietnam News Agency said today.
   The official agency said the service would be operated by the
Vietnam Red Cross, which has already held courses in cooperation
with the International Committe of the Red Cross.
   The service would not incorporate the search for American MIAs or
the children of Vietnamese-American parents, the news agency said.
   The report did not say whether the Red Cross would actually
search for remains of those killed in decades of warfare in Vietnam
or just act as a tracing service for families separated by war and
other disasters.
</TEXT>
