<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--WilsonQuints     02-04 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Wilson Quints,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Wilson Quintuplets Sent Home From Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two of the quintuplets born last month to their
autoworker parents rode home in a limousine equipped with infant
safety seats, but their siblings could remain hospitalized until
early spring.
   The limousine left Sinai Hospital Friday afternoon with Anthony
and Rebecca Wilson on board. Anthony now weighs 4 pounds and 9
ounces and Rebecca, 4 pounds and 2 ounces. The five babies' weights
ranged from 2 pounds, 9 ounces to 3 pounds, 7 ounces at birth.
   Mary Jo Wilson of Auburn Hills delivered the quintuplets about
nine weeks prematurely on Jan. 5. The other three, Shelby, Elizabeth
and Cameron, remained at Sinai in good condition, hospital officials
said.
   Mrs. Wilson, 30, said she took fertility drugs to help her
conceive. She and her husband Billy, 34, also have a 2-year-old son.
The Wilsons work at the General Motors Corp. Truck and Bus Plant in
Pontiac.
