<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Cat'sHouse     02-04 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Cat's House,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cat For Sale For $236,000, With House Tossed In</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARKET DRAYTON, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Figaro the cat is on the market
for $236,250 _ the only catch is that the house goes with him.
   Peter Glanfield, a business consultant, said the black-and-white
Persian feline ``adopted'' his four-bedroom home in this central
England town several years ago, and he called it unfair to separate
Figaro from it.
   So the cat's picture was printed on the front of home's real
estate flier, and prospective buyers were warned they cannot buy the
house without Figaro.
   ``The elegant feline comes complete with a freehold Victorian
residence of character in order to keep him in the style to which he
is accustomed,'' said the flier, which described Figaro as a ``large
friendly cat.''
   ``It really is a case of no puss, no purchase,'' real estate
agent Richard Taylor said Friday.

</TEXT>
