<HEAD>Attorney General Vows To Get Tough Against Drug Traffickers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Attorney General Dick Thornburgh vowed Saturday
to take a ``rougher, tougher attitude'' toward violent drug
traffickers to achieve President Bush's goal of a ``kindler, gentler
America.''
   In a speech prepared for delivery to the American Judicature
Society and the National Conference of Bar Presidents meeting in
Denver, Thornburgh decried the number of drug-related murders in
American cities, notably in the nation's capital where 60 percent of
the 369 killings last year were narcotics related.
