activities, including application of the newly-enacted federal death
penalty will be necessary to end the `free-fire' zones that have
taken the lives of innocent people, including an increasing number
of young people,'' Thornburg said.
   ``Achieving President Bush's `kindler, gentler America' will
require a `rougher, tougher' attitude toward some Americans _ those
who engage in crimes of violence associated with the drug trade and
with urban terrorism,'' he said.
   An advance copy of the speech was released in Washington.
