<HEAD>Five Children Die In Measles Epidemic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A measles epidemic in the Portuguese
capital has killed five children, and 200 have been hospitalized,
the country's news agency said Saturday.
   Lusa quoted an official of the independent doctors' trade union
as saying the death toll could be higher.
   Dr. Jose Manuel Trindade said the measles outbreak was caused by
the Health Ministry's failure to provide a vaccination program, Lusa
reported.
   He said the union will transfer more doctors to children's
hospitals to help fight the epidemic. If doctors go ahead with a
three-day strike scheduled to start Wednesday, infected children
should be transferred to military hospitals, Trindade said.
   Doctors' unions and the government are at odds over a plan to
restructure health services.
