<FIRST>r a AM-FatalFires     02-04 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Fatal Fires,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Separate Fires Kill Four In Grand Rapids Suburb</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KENTWOOD, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two separate fires believed to have both
started in chimneys killed four people and critically injured a
fifth person early Saturday in this Grand Rapids suburb, authorities
said.
   The fires broke out within a 2{-hour period in homes of nearly
identical construction located about two miles apart, Fire Chief
Bill Thornton said. Both apparently began in chimneys, he said.
   ``The layout of the houses are identical. The interiors were
built the same; the stairways in the same way; the victims were
found in the same location of (each) house,'' Thornton said. ``There
were a lot of coincidences.''
   The first blaze killed Theresa Porter, 32; her 3-year-old son,
Andrew, and 13-month-old daughter, Jennifer, officials said. The
woman's husband, Hugh, was not home at the time.
   The victim of the second fire was identified as Dolores Berggren,
35. Her husband, David, 49, rescued their two young daughters before
being admitted to Blodgett Memorial Medical Center in Grand Rapids,
where he was listed in critical condition Saturday night with burns
over 70 percent of his body.
</TEXT>
